<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-03-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="802" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.21/698: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Colombian Minister of Foreign Affairs</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Uribe</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogota</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-01"><hi rend="italic">March 1,
                                1922</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received March 3.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have the honor to inform Your Excellency that on this day the exchange
                            of ratifications of the Treaty of April 6, 1914, between Colombia and
                            the United States of America was effected. The relations of cordial
                            friendship which so long existed between the two nations are thus
                            restored.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Antonio José
                            Uribe</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>